\begin_layout Standard
The third group is very high income earners who have considerably more income than necessary to satisfy basic necessities,
 are able to indulge in luxury consumption and accumulate wealth,
 and indirectly power.
 For this group (a combination of capitalists,
 rentiers and a few ‘workers’ with special talents and very high incomes),
 once consumption needs
